00:12:14.730 --> 00:12:16.995
for gestational hypertension,

263
00:12:16.995 --> 00:12:19.530
one of those being preeclampsia,

264
00:12:19.530 --> 00:12:20.615
increased risk of cesarean delivery

265
00:12:20.615 --> 00:12:23.232
and you have an increased risk of developing diabetes

266
00:12:23.232 --> 00:12:25.377
in that infant later in life.

267
00:12:25.377 --> 00:12:28.956
Now, how do we detect gestational diabetes?

268
00:12:28.956 --> 00:12:32.233
I want you to focus on the USPSTF 2021.

269
00:12:32.233 --> 00:12:34.833
Everybody gets screened at 24 weeks.

270
00:12:37.135 --> 00:12:41.870
The USPSTF says there's current evidence is insufficient

271
00:12:41.870 --> 00:12:44.733
as to whether you should screen the first prenatal visit.

272
00:12:45.740 --> 00:12:48.354
The ADA and the ACOG say,

273
00:12:48.354 --> 00:12:50.611
yeah, you should screen at the first prenatal visit.

274
00:12:50.611 --> 00:12:52.751
Now, you are looking for gestational diabetes

275
00:12:52.751 --> 00:12:55.481
because it's carbohydrate intolerance first diagnosed

276
00:12:55.481 --> 00:12:56.929
during pregnancy.

277
00:12:56.929 --> 00:13:01.929
But basically, what you're screening for is type 2 diabetes.

278
00:13:02.242 --> 00:13:06.660
And the question is, do I change the outcome by doing that?

279
00:13:06.660 --> 00:13:09.240
And there, the data is insufficient.

280
00:13:09.240 --> 00:13:11.128
But here are the risk factors.

281
00:13:11.128 --> 00:13:14.057
As for anybody where you're looking for type 2 diabetes,

282
00:13:14.057 --> 00:13:16.235
it's just it's first diagnosed during pregnancy

283
00:13:16.235 --> 00:13:18.471
so by definition is gestational.

284
00:13:18.471 --> 00:13:19.740
These are the risk factors

285
00:13:19.740 --> 00:13:23.513
by which you would screen anyone who was younger, okay?

286
00:13:27.483 --> 00:13:29.501
Now, the two-step approach is typically used

287
00:13:29.501 --> 00:13:31.990
whether you're screening at the first prenatal visit

288
00:13:31.990 --> 00:13:33.369
or at 24 weeks.

289
00:13:33.369 --> 00:13:36.030
Remember, if you screen at the first prenatal visit

290
00:13:36.030 --> 00:13:38.609
and it's negative, you would rescreen at 24 weeks

291
00:13:38.609 --> 00:13:40.371
because gestational diabetes,

292
00:13:40.371 --> 00:13:43.173
the risk develops as pregnancy moves forward.

293
00:13:46.476 --> 00:13:49.743
We do an initial screen with a 50-gram oral glucose load.

294
00:13:50.620 --> 00:13:51.856
You don't need to know the numbers.

295
00:13:51.856 --> 00:13:53.520
Just know if it's abnormal,

296
00:13:53.520 --> 00:13:55.593
they go on to a diagnostic evaluation.

297
00:13:56.502 --> 00:13:58.744
I will tell you, if on the initial screen,

298
00:13:58.744 --> 00:14:02.989
it's greater than 190, most people will not do a three-hour

299
00:14:02.989 --> 00:14:04.953
because it's gonna be positive.

300
00:14:06.610 --> 00:14:08.983
The three-hour oral glucose tolerance test is done

301
00:14:08.983 --> 00:14:10.975
as the diagnostic test.

302
00:14:10.975 --> 00:14:13.995
So you do an overnight fast, you check the blood sugar.

303
00:14:13.995 --> 00:14:16.231
That's blood sugar number one of four.

304
00:14:16.231 --> 00:14:18.341
You then give 'em a hundred-gram glucose load

305
00:14:18.341 --> 00:14:20.076
and then you check a blood sugar one hour,

306
00:14:20.076 --> 00:14:21.343
two hours, three hours.

307
00:14:21.343 --> 00:14:24.859
If one over two of those values or the fasting was abnormal,

308
00:14:24.859 --> 00:14:29.859
they have diagnostic criteria met for gestational diabetes

309
00:14:30.352 --> 00:14:32.760
or carbohydrate intolerance first diagnosed

310
00:14:32.760 --> 00:14:33.873
during pregnancy.

311
00:14:34.723 --> 00:14:39.210
The screening test can be done non-fasting.

312
00:14:39.210 --> 00:14:42.210
And it typically is. Patient's just there, you have it done.

313
00:14:43.869 --> 00:14:48.869
Now, screening later in pregnancy, open neural tube defects,

314
00:14:49.224 --> 00:14:53.225
aneuploidy, screening sonogram, anemia, and group B strep.

315
00:14:53.225 --> 00:14:56.486
Okay. So neural tube defects.

316
00:14:56.486 --> 00:14:59.848
Here, we're doing a maternal serum alpha-fetoprotein.

317
00:14:59.848 --> 00:15:02.073
This is a blood test on mom.

318
00:15:02.989 --> 00:15:05.247
If it's high, it may indicate an open neural tube defect.

319
00:15:05.247 --> 00:15:08.359
This is a calculated risk.

320
00:15:08.359 --> 00:15:10.757
It's most accurately done between 16 and 18 weeks.

321
00:15:10.757 --> 00:15:14.341
The most common reason is I have an incorrect assignment

322
00:15:14.341 --> 00:15:16.373
of the estimated gestational age, you know?

