00:25:37.499 --> 00:25:41.727
Now, here are the risk factors for ectopic, okay?

518
00:25:41.727 --> 00:25:44.520
Prior sterilization, previous tubal surgery.

519
00:25:44.520 --> 00:25:45.487
Anything you've done to that tube,

520
00:25:45.487 --> 00:25:47.731
you're gonna increase the risk.

521
00:25:47.731 --> 00:25:51.243
Now, typically, these patients are gonna present

522
00:25:51.243 --> 00:25:53.743
about seven weeks.

523
00:25:53.743 --> 00:25:56.373
They'll get pain and then bleeding.

524
00:25:57.988 --> 00:26:00.450
The diagnostic test of choice is an ultrasound,

525
00:26:00.450 --> 00:26:02.750
but these are the two numbers you need to see.

526
00:26:04.120 --> 00:26:07.001
If you have a hCG greater than 3,500,

527
00:26:07.001 --> 00:26:09.009
you should see a gestational sac

528
00:26:09.009 --> 00:26:11.250
on transabdominal ultrasound.

529
00:26:11.250 --> 00:26:14.988
If you don't, you've got an ectopic until proven otherwise.

530
00:26:14.988 --> 00:26:17.992
If the hCG is greater than 1,800,

531
00:26:17.992 --> 00:26:21.232
you should see a gestational sac on transvaginal ultrasound.

532
00:26:21.232 --> 00:26:23.004
If you don't, you have an ectopic.

533
00:26:23.004 --> 00:26:27.217
So, our patient had an hCG greater than 1,800,

534
00:26:27.217 --> 00:26:29.010
so there's no reason to repeat it.

535
00:26:29.010 --> 00:26:30.492
You know it's ectopic.

536
00:26:30.492 --> 00:26:31.992
If it were less than 1,800,

537
00:26:31.992 --> 00:26:35.250
that's when you would repeat the ultrasound.

538
00:26:35.250 --> 00:26:38.618
Now, beta-hCG, if it increases by doubling,

539
00:26:38.618 --> 00:26:40.518
which is really 53%,

540
00:26:40.518 --> 00:26:43.258
does that mean it's an intrauterine pregnancy, not ectopic?

541
00:26:43.258 --> 00:26:44.223
No.

542
00:26:45.242 --> 00:26:46.492
Diagnostic curettage,

543
00:26:46.492 --> 00:26:50.560
if you know that the patient has an ectopic

544
00:26:51.848 --> 00:26:54.725
and the hCG levels are falling,

545
00:26:54.725 --> 00:26:56.239
you can do a diagnostic curettage

546
00:26:56.239 --> 00:26:57.748
because if you don't have chorionic villi,

547
00:26:57.748 --> 00:26:59.583
you know you have an ectopic.

548
00:27:00.730 --> 00:27:02.488
Hemodynamically unstable patient,

549
00:27:02.488 --> 00:27:05.999
they are going to need have an immediate surgery.

550
00:27:05.999 --> 00:27:08.476
Early diagnosis and the patient is stable,

551
00:27:08.476 --> 00:27:11.266
you can do medical management with methotrexate.

552
00:27:11.266 --> 00:27:15.060
This is an agent, which is a folic acid antagonist,

553
00:27:15.060 --> 00:27:17.376
and it inhibits DNA synthesis and cell replication.

554
00:27:17.376 --> 00:27:18.855
Well, there's a lot of that going on

555
00:27:18.855 --> 00:27:21.620
in this particular environment.

556
00:27:21.620 --> 00:27:24.011
So, it selectively kills cytotrophoblast.

557
00:27:24.011 --> 00:27:28.110
These are the rapidly dividing cells, the implantation site,

558
00:27:28.110 --> 00:27:31.410
and then your body will just spontaneously reabsorb it.

559
00:27:31.410 --> 00:27:33.366
We've been designed well.

560
00:27:33.366 --> 00:27:35.733
Now, here's the scoop,

561
00:27:36.730 --> 00:27:38.479
you measure the beta-hCG levels

562
00:27:38.479 --> 00:27:42.259
on days four and seven after the methotrexate.

563
00:27:42.259 --> 00:27:46.994
If the difference in decrease is greater than 15%,

564
00:27:46.994 --> 00:27:48.753
you just follow it down.

565
00:27:50.244 --> 00:27:53.485
If the difference in decrease is less than 15%,

566
00:27:53.485 --> 00:27:55.533
you would give another dose.

567
00:27:58.986 --> 00:28:02.613
If it's going up, you gotta intervene.

568
00:28:02.613 --> 00:28:04.613
And that was the issue with our patient.

569
00:28:07.995 --> 00:28:10.613
We'd like to do a salpingostomy.

570
00:28:10.613 --> 00:28:13.470
Now, if you're doing a salpingostomy,

571
00:28:13.470 --> 00:28:16.290
you may not get rid of all the products of conception,

572
00:28:16.290 --> 00:28:18.233
so if a salpingostomy has been done,

573
00:28:18.233 --> 00:28:20.471
or you're given that on the exam,

574
00:28:20.471 --> 00:28:25.471
you've gotta check the beta-hCG level weekly till it's zero.

575
00:28:28.361 --> 00:28:30.607
If you do a salpingectomy,

576
00:28:30.607 --> 00:28:32.490
you go in and cut out everything,

577
00:28:32.490 --> 00:28:34.875
then you've removed all the products of conception.

578
00:28:34.875 --> 00:28:36.474
You can't leave anything behind.

579
00:28:36.474 --> 00:28:37.980
But with the salpingostomy,

580
00:28:37.980 --> 00:28:41.503
you're basically just removing the gunk, we'll call it,

581
00:28:41.503 --> 00:28:44.245
like a tube, like a plumbing tube

582
00:28:44.245 --> 00:28:46.290
and leaving the tube in place.

583
00:28:46.290 --> 00:28:47.237
Well, that means you could leave a little bit

584
00:28:47.237 --> 00:28:49.109
of residual there.

585
00:28:49.109 --> 00:28:51.624
Please, in no way am I saying that that embryo is gunk.

586
00:28:51.624 --> 00:28:52.860
That's not what I mean here,

587
00:28:52.860 --> 00:28:55.710
but, you know, I'm just using that as an example.

588
00:28:55.710 --> 00:28:56.543
Okay.

589
00:28:59.994 --> 00:29:03.488
Okay. Here are the recommendations for practice.

590
00:29:03.488 --> 00:29:05.734
First trimester bleeding,

591
00:29:05.734 --> 00:29:08.231
ectopic, spontaneous pregnancy loss.

592
00:29:08.231 --> 00:29:10.116
Chromosomal abnormalities are 50

593
00:29:10.116 --> 00:29:13.500
or cause 50% of spontaneous pregnancy losses.

594
00:29:13.500 --> 00:29:14.747
No bed rest/drug therapy

595
00:29:14.747 --> 00:29:16.803
will correct these common etiologies.

596
00:29:17.971 --> 00:29:21.235
Most women will have one spontaneous loss in their life.

597
00:29:21.235 --> 00:29:22.376
A lot of them never even know it

598
00:29:22.376 --> 00:29:24.397
because, you know, they're two weeks late.

599
00:29:24.397 --> 00:29:26.118
"Oh (sighs), thank goodness I wasn't pregnant,"

600
00:29:26.118 --> 00:29:27.270
but they really were.

601
00:29:27.270 --> 00:29:28.474
Okay.

602
00:29:28.474 --> 00:29:30.991
Okay, our last AES question.

603
00:29:30.991 --> 00:29:33.724
For which one of the following conditions

604
00:29:33.724 --> 00:29:35.130
is there good evidence

605
00:29:35.130 --> 00:29:37.500
for the routine administration of anti-D immune globulin

606
00:29:37.500 --> 00:29:39.737
to an unsensitized, D-negative patient?

607
00:29:39.737 --> 00:29:41.924
First-trimester pregnancy loss, abdominal trauma,

608
00:29:41.924 --> 00:29:43.495
second or third-trimester antenatal bleeding

609
00:29:43.495 --> 00:29:45.753
or attempting an external cephalic version?

610
00:29:50.737 --> 00:29:52.003
Okay, let's see here.

611
00:29:52.003 --> 00:29:55.290
Good. 60% of you knew the answer.

612
00:29:55.290 --> 00:29:58.023
It's after a first-trimester pregnancy loss. Okay.

613
00:29:59.246 --> 00:30:02.981
So here is the scoop. Here is the level A evidence.

614
00:30:02.981 --> 00:30:04.890
We give it to everybody at 28 weeks

615
00:30:04.890 --> 00:30:06.359
unless you know the father of the baby

616
00:30:06.359 --> 00:30:09.477
is going to be also be Rh-negative.

617
00:30:09.477 --> 00:30:11.501
But you know, I've had patients come in,

618
00:30:11.501 --> 00:30:12.742
you know, and argue with me.

619
00:30:12.742 --> 00:30:16.865
The mother's arguing with me. "I cannot be 24 weeks."

620
00:30:16.865 --> 00:30:18.763
And then the gentleman there with her says,

621
00:30:18.763 --> 00:30:20.248
"Of course, she can't be 24 weeks.

622
00:30:20.248 --> 00:30:22.240
We've only known each other for 10 weeks."

623
00:30:22.240 --> 00:30:25.323
(attendees laughing)

624
00:30:26.235 --> 00:30:29.880
Within 72 hours after the delivery of an Rh-positive infant,

625
00:30:29.880 --> 00:30:33.270
if his mom is negative, first trimester's pregnancy lost

626
00:30:33.270 --> 00:30:34.953
after an invasive procedure.

627
00:30:35.894 --> 00:30:38.880
Level C, threatened abortion,

628
00:30:38.880 --> 00:30:40.731
second or third trimester antenatal bleeding,

629
00:30:40.731 --> 00:30:42.270
external cephalic version.

630
00:30:42.270 --> 00:30:43.103
I love the ALSO Manual.

631
00:30:43.103 --> 00:30:46.740
It says this is minimally uncomfortable for the mother.

632
00:30:46.740 --> 00:30:49.494
Okay, this is like having a wrestling match with the mother

633
00:30:49.494 --> 00:30:52.020
and a baby from outside.

634
00:30:52.020 --> 00:30:55.770
And then any abdominal trauma. That's level C.

635
00:30:55.770 --> 00:30:57.540
Practice recommendations, that's our summary.

636
00:30:57.540 --> 00:30:59.927
Put those with your study materials, and we are done.

637
00:30:59.927 --> 00:31:01.004
Thank you very much.

638
00:31:01.004 --> 00:31:02.628
(attendees clapping)

639
00:31:02.628 --> 00:31:05.378
(ethereal music)

